text:
Oh, Gura, on the off chance you read this, you mentioned you were having sync issues with Hi-Fi Rush. The best advice I can give you is to go wired with everything you're using. That's not just your controller or keyboard/mouse that includes your headphones. Plug everything in directly with a wire to reduce input delay and headphone latency to as close to 0 as possible. I was having issues with delay as big as a 1/16th note while my headphones were wireless, which would probably be fine on Normal but I'm playing on Very Hard which needs tighter timing and hitting where I hear the beat was a fail. However, when I plugged my headphones in with a wire I couldn't notice a delay at all and I could just listen instead of look for visual cues.

tl;dr wired keyboard/mouse/controller AND wired headphones.
